<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{ppoi}}</strong> is used as a suffix to indicate that something has a distinctive characteristic of an attribute
identified by the noun, adjective or verb stem.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{konnna@KJ{{water}}<strong>ppoi</strong>@KJ{{sake}}, @KJ{{drink}}naizo.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Who can drink such watery sake?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{anata, konnna@KJ{{relax}}<strong>ppoi</strong>@KT{{sofua}}wo@KJ{{buy}}ttekitesousuruno?}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What are you going to do with that cheapish sofa that yo ubought?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{juutanha @KJ{{dirty}}re<strong>ppoi</strong>kara, @KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{use}}tteimasen.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Carpte gets dirty easily, so I'm not using it.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{ppoi}}</strong> conjugates as an @HI{{i}}-adjective.
</p>

